  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations. In the United States, key laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act, which require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions and implement compliance programs. Most developed countries have similar legislation designed to prevent criminal financial activities. These laws typically require banks and other financial institutions to conduct customer due diligence, monitor transactions, and report large or suspicious financial activities to authorities.",
